parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request.

You can use the client to generate the token, but you must make sure that the token is unique among all requests. The token can contain only ASCII characters.

> If you do not specify this parameter, the system automatically uses the **request ID** as the **client token**. The **request ID** may be different for each request.

parameters.name: EndpointGroupId
parameters.description: The ID of the endpoint group to which the endpoint that you want to delete belongs.

parameters.name: EndpointIds
parameters.description:
The IDs of endpoints to be deleted.

If you do not set this parameter, all the endpoints in the specified endpoint group are deleted.

You can specify at most 10 endpoint IDs.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description: The region ID of the GA instance. Set the value to **cn-hangzhou**.
